Now, the story of the microwave oven is quite a special one.

00:05:24.674 --> 00:05:32.589
In 1945, just as World War II was ending, there was a self-taught engineer called Percy Spencer.

00:05:34.149 --> 00:05:40.669
He was working with radar technology for the Allies, and one day, as

00:05:40.679 --> 00:05:46.759
he was working with a radar, he reached down into his pocket, and found

00:05:47.079 --> 00:05:52.299
that the peanut candy bar that he had there had completely melted.

00:05:53.649 --> 00:06:00.799
The temperature of the room wasn’t hot enough to have melted it, and this bar had completely melted.

00:06:01.589 --> 00:06:05.759
Spencer realised that it must have been the radar that did it.

00:06:06.949 --> 00:06:15.439
The radar machine must have emitted microwaves that had the effect of heating substances.

00:06:17.029 --> 00:06:24.989
So, the legend goes, Spencer immediately went away with some corn, and then put it

00:06:24.989 --> 00:06:32.509
next to the radar, and the corn started popping, much like you see in popcorn machines.

00:06:33.519 --> 00:06:40.079
The next day, he came back with an egg, and he  it next to the radar to see what would happen.

00:06:41.339 --> 00:06:46.769
And if you have ever put an egg in a microwave, you will know what happened.

00:06:47.159 --> 00:06:49.329
It exploded in his face.

00:06:50.209 --> 00:06:53.239
So he had discovered the microwave oven.

00:06:55.229 --> 00:06:56.654
Shortly after this, he went and filed a patent for it.

00:06:56.709 --> 00:07:02.239
And then two years later, the first commercial microwave oven came on sale.

00:07:03.729 --> 00:07:08.979
It was a little different to the one that you and I would recognise now though - it

00:07:08.979 --> 00:07:15.774
was almost 2 metres tall, and cost today's equivalent of around $50,000.

00:07:17.149 --> 00:07:19.579
So it wasn't an immediate success.

00:07:20.089 --> 00:07:25.162
However, as the technology improved, the boxes became smaller and smaller,

00:07:25.622 --> 00:07:29.702
and they were soon affordable to the growing American middle class.

00:07:30.302 --> 00:07:36.082
And within a few years, It was being sold into households all over America.

