00:10:17.814 --> 00:10:21.494
Our penultimate invention is something called velcro.

00:10:22.604 --> 00:10:27.784
Now, velcro, in case you don’t know what it is, is the material that you

00:10:27.844 --> 00:10:34.414
often find to fasten two things together, to attach two things together.

00:10:34.534 --> 00:10:41.894
Often children’s shoes use this to tighten the shoes without using laces - it is normally

00:10:41.924 --> 00:10:50.425
black, and one side is fluffy, it’s hairy, and the other side is full of tiny little hooks.

00:10:52.045 --> 00:10:55.855
But how Velcro came into existence is an interesting

00:10:55.855 --> 00:11:01.478
story, and the heroes of our story are a man and a dog.

00:11:02.818 --> 00:11:09.508
Now, those of you that have dogs, especially dogs with lots of hair, will know that

00:11:09.668 --> 00:11:15.708
if they run in long grass, they tend to return with lots of little things stuck

00:11:15.708 --> 00:11:20.788
to them, which can be difficult to remove, depending on how hairy your dog is.

00:11:22.708 --> 00:11:29.008
A Swiss engineer, a man called George de Mestral was out walking with his

00:11:29.008 --> 00:11:35.358
dog, and he noticed that these little things kept sticking to his dog's hair.

00:11:36.708 --> 00:11:44.948
He was curious about how that actually worked, and so, being a curious mind, he looked under

00:11:44.948 --> 00:11:51.608
the microscope back in his laboratory, and saw that each of these little things that was stuck

00:11:51.658 --> 00:11:59.398
to his dog had tiny, tiny, little hooks that had caught in his dog’s hair, in his dog's fur.

00:12:00.788 --> 00:12:07.438
He thought, well, if I can create this artificially, using synthetic material,

00:12:07.898 --> 00:12:12.838
that would be great - it would be another way of fastening two things together.

00:12:14.508 --> 00:12:18.948
He created the first version of velcro - one side was fluffy,

00:12:18.948 --> 00:12:22.748
and the other side was full of thousands of tiny little hooks.

00:12:23.288 --> 00:12:26.918
So when they were pressed together, they stuck.

00:12:27.548 --> 00:12:30.418
You had to pull hard to remove one from the other.

00:12:31.608 --> 00:12:32.908
Velcro was born.

00:12:34.438 --> 00:12:41.538
However, it wasn't an immediate hit, and it took years until it actually became popular.

00:12:42.998 --> 00:12:48.648
Interestingly enough, one of the first really popular uses of Velcro, or at

00:12:48.648 --> 00:12:55.555
least one of the ways in which Velcro became known around the world was through

00:12:55.975 --> 00:13:03.405
astronauts - for astronauts it was a very easy way to attach things when they

00:13:03.405 --> 00:13:07.595
were wearing these large space suits, so they couldn't really use their hands.

00:13:08.045 --> 00:13:16.870
Our final invention story is of the stethoscope, the device that doctors use to listen to the

00:13:16.880 --> 00:13:24.120
beating of your heart, the device that’s essentially a long tube with a metal piece that is

00:13:24.160 --> 00:13:30.530
pressed against your chest, and the tube divides into two parts that go into the doctor’s ear.

00:13:31.680 --> 00:13:32.120
Got it?

00:13:32.970 --> 00:13:33.300
Great.

00:13:34.430 --> 00:13:39.930
Now, this story takes us back to the year 1816, to France,

00:13:40.320 --> 00:13:43.560
to the doctor's surgery of a man called René Laennec.

00:13:45.270 --> 00:13:51.460
In his clinic was a young woman who was quite overweight, she was a bit fat.

00:13:52.680 --> 00:13:56.990
The normal thing that a doctor would have done would have been to

00:13:57.030 --> 00:14:02.930
check her heart just by placing his or her ear over the chest of the

00:14:02.930 --> 00:14:08.400
patient, however there were two problems with this particular woman.

00:14:09.940 --> 00:14:15.280
The first problem was that she was a young woman, and it would have been

00:14:15.340 --> 00:14:21.390
embarrassing for a male doctor to have put his ear directly to her bare chest.

00:14:22.280 --> 00:14:27.800
So he didn’t want to put her in an awkward position, he didn’t want to embarrass her.

00:14:29.250 --> 00:14:33.730
The second problem was that she was overweight, and it

00:14:33.770 --> 00:14:38.160
would have been difficult to accurately hear her heartbeat.

00:14:39.740 --> 00:14:45.510
So our hero, the inventor of the stethoscope, Dr Laennec had an idea.

00:14:46.830 --> 00:14:51.300
He had previously seen school children playing a game where they

00:14:51.300 --> 00:14:55.290
used a hollow stick, a stick with a hole through the middle.

00:14:56.430 --> 00:15:04.560
In this game, one child put their ear on one end of the stick, and the other child scratched

00:15:04.600 --> 00:15:11.899
the other end with a pin, so they made a noise at the other end, Dr Laennec thought,

00:15:12.339 --> 00:15:18.599
well, it seems like I might be able to hear more clearly, and cause this patient less

00:15:18.619 --> 00:15:26.429
embarrassment if I do a similar thing, and so he went and found some paper, rolled it up into

00:15:26.429 --> 00:15:33.539
a cylinder, and pressed one end to the young woman's chest, and the other end to his ear.

00:15:34.307 --> 00:15:41.837
Ta-da, he could hear her heartbeat distinctly, and the first-ever stethoscope had been invented.

00:15:43.737 --> 00:15:50.287
It has of course evolved a bit since then, but the principle, from an acoustic point

00:15:50.287 --> 00:15:56.477
of view, at least is the same - create a tube, and you can hear a sound more clearly

00:15:56.547 --> 00:16:02.547
if you listen through the tube than if you just put your ear directly at the end.

00:16:03.487 --> 00:16:04.397
Amazing, right?

00:16:05.197 --> 00:16:09.637
A device that is now used by millions of doctors all over the world,

00:16:10.057 --> 00:16:15.577
and no doubt has saved millions of lives, was discovered almost by

00:16:15.577 --> 00:16:20.097
accident after a doctor saw some children playing a game with a tube.

00:16:21.487 --> 00:16:24.807
I, for one, think that is a pretty fun story.

